ENVIRONMENT — Verifiable Accounting Arithmetic reference implementation

TOOLCHAIN
  rust: 1.85.0 (pinned via rust-toolchain.toml)
  cargo: bundled with the pinned rustc
  target triples tested: x86_64-pc-windows-msvc, x86_64-unknown-linux-gnu, aarch64-apple-darwin

KEY DEPENDENCIES
  Versions below state the workspace minimum; exact resolved versions live in Cargo.lock.

  Cryptography
    secp256k1        >= 0.29   (Rust binding to libsecp256k1, Bitcoin Core's reference C implementation)
    secp256k1-zkp    TBD       (Rust binding to libsecp256k1-zkp, Blockstream fork; introduced in step 3 for Pedersen + Bulletproofs)
    sha2             >= 0.10   (RustCrypto SHA-256; used for the BSV double-SHA256 primitive)

  BSV / Bitcoin types
    bitcoin          TBD       (rust-bitcoin; consensus-layer compatible with BSV for txid / header / Merkle / basic script)
    Replace or augment with a maintained BSV-specific library if needed; record choice and rationale in docs/DECISIONS.md.

  Encoding / serialization
    serde, serde_json, ciborium, hex, hex-literal

  Errors / utilities
    thiserror, anyhow

  CLI
    clap (derive)

  Testing / benchmarks
    proptest, criterion

NETWORKS
  Default test/CI: offline only. All vectors are committed to /vectors.
  Optional live verification path against BSV mainnet / testnet headers is provided behind a feature flag,
  not enabled in CI.

HARDWARE FOR BENCHMARKS
  TBD — populated when the first benchmark run is captured in /bench. The benchmark harness reports
  median and IQR over many iterations on named hardware; no transactions-per-second figure is extrapolated.

REPRODUCIBILITY
  See docs/REPRODUCIBILITY.md for the exact commands to regenerate every value the paper cites.
